@{b}About ASWPOP@{ub}
------------

ASWPOP is a POP3 compliant mail receiver client.. WITH A DIFFERENCE!! :) and
let's get something clear, when I say 'With a difference', I don't mean "Oh,
all the other POP clients are amazing and this one's total sludge!".. no,
not in the least! :) I'm saying that this is the most highly user
configurable POP client I've ever come in contact with (and I've tried a
few!)..

YES.. it's coded in AREXX... you may laugh, but AREXX is one heck of a
powerful language, and if you ask me, is AmigaDOS's most underatted and
powerful asset. Let's see a pissy user with my capacity for programming
(sadly, rather limited!) knock up a POP client for it's machine!? :-) ho ho
ho.. anyways:

@{b}Requirements@{ub}
------------

ASWPOP requires Amitcp (for the TCP: device), AREXX (WB2 and above then!), a
live connection to a POP3 server and of course, you have to have a POP
mailbox account!

As far as I know, ASWPOP requires no special processor or memory
requirements.. it should be perfectly happy running on a 1mb FDD A600..

@{b}Features of ASWPOP include:@{ub}
---------------------------

     1) -- Small and easy to setup


     2) -- Internal functions allowing you to KILL/HIGHLIGHT or REDIRECT
           emails to other boxes depending on the FROM or SUBJECT field.
           eg.. If 2 users wanted to share one POP account, ASWPOP could be
           configured to say, send all messages with the subject "tome" to
           a mailfile of your choice.


     3) -- Powerful function whereupon a user of ASWPOP can write his/her
           own scripts and have them executed when a match between a
           FROM/SUBJECT line to search for (specified in a prefs file) and
           the current FROM/SUBJECT or TO line in the message being
           downloaded is found... These scripts can be either Internally run
           (Your scripts act as if they are hardcoded into ASWPOP, allowing
           you full access to the program variables) or Externally run,
           meaning you can not only use scripts, but can use standalone
           executables with the ability to specify a command line

     4) -- Can be given a list of POP servers to check, each with it's own
           login/password/mailbox arguments.

     5) -- A programmer who is extremely keen to develop this program far
           past the level it is today, but is buggered if he has any fresh
           ideas! :)

So, basically I'm selling ASWPOP on it's ability to be "added" to by the
average miggy user! (a damn fine Bloke/Blokess!).. You will find a couple
of my very own scripts included, to demonstrate how to write your own...

ASWPOP is sendmesomemoneyifyouwant-ware... I am releasing this as PD, for the
good of the world! :-) But any donations, be it money, sex or whatever will
be gratefully received... Developing a program such as this does require a lot
of online time, and in my situation, online time is VERY expensive :(( So, if
you really like ASWPOP (what are you, some sort of nutter!?!) and donating a
small amount won't put you out of pocket, then go ahead.. email me and you'll
be straight on my christmas card list! :-)

That's it then.. on with the game, eh?

