@{b}Usage@{ub}
-----

Okey dokey, you've installed it, tweaked the config files, now you're itching
to receive some mail.. (hehe) are we rapidly turning into a world of net
freaks? Nah.. course we're not.. anyways, link up to the net and start ASWPOP
by simply finding the path to ASWPOP in a shell and running it... (the
script bit needs to be set).. You stop the thing by sending a Control+C into
the shell window..

I know it's messy, but I will improve things in later releases..

Currently, the only command line option is to specify which STARTUPMODE to
use.. (one specified in the command line supercedes the line in the prefs
file) eg: aswpop once

@{b}The report window@{ub}
-----------------

ASWPOP uses a CON window that pops up on the Workbench screen to tell you
what's going on..it's all pretty simple to understand.. after executing, it
will say:

Started ASWPOP with mode "CONTCHECK".... (or ONCE, depending on the prefs
file or command line)

Then, it will attempt to connect to your server, and tell you how many mails
are waiting collection.. if there are none, it tells you and quits if
STARTUPMODE is set to ONCE, or waits before trying again if set to
CONTCHECK..

If there is an error in the works, ASWPOP will beep your display and tell
you about it.. a list of all the errors and possible causes/fixes can be
found in @{"Troubleshooting " Link "Troubleshooting"}

On receiving a Control+C, ASWPOP will cleanly break the connection, update
you in the logwindow and execute the POSTPULL line if set..

Hopefully all is well up to now! :-)

