@{b}Why doesn't the bugger work!!@{ub}
-----------------------------

ASWPOP is by no means 100% safe!! Infact, early beta releases were really
quite appalling! Now though, it is approaching something approaching
stability.. I haven't suffered an error in days, and I receive 20-70k of
UUencoded mail each day.. Nevertheless, errors are all part of a program's
development, there is bound to be some in there somewhere, and so I'll be
very gratefull to hear of any problems/errors you have with ASWPOP... who
knows, someday this program might be good!

Anyway, here is the full list of errors and their causes and possible
solutions:

@{b}"List failed"@{ub}

ASWPOP requested the list of all mails waiting on the POP server but wasn't
fed with them.. this is more than likely a weird POP3 server, and if this
error pops up, I'd like to hear from you!! (I've never encountered it
myself)

@{b}"Cannot open mailbox"@{ub}

ASWPOP had problems opening your mailbox.. either the path to your mailbox
is invalid, (check in s:aswpop.prefs) or some other program/task has a lock
on the file.. shut down all systems that might have a lock and retry.

@{b}"Connection to POP Server has failed"@{ub}

ASWPOP couldn't connect to your specified POP3 server on the specified
port.. you could have misspelled the server name, check s:aswpop.prefs to
see if it is valid.. Also, you might not be linked up to the internet, the
POP server might be out of order or you might not be using Amitcp with the
TCP: device mounted!

@{b}"Oops.. this isn't a POP3 server"@{ub}

ASWPOP has connected to the host, but the host isn't running a POP3 server
on the port connected to.. Check your port number and POPSERVER line in
aswpop.prefs and try again.

@{b}"Login failed.."@{ub}

ASWPOP has succesfully connected to a POP server running on the host, BUT
your login has failed.. check you have set the correct username and password
in aswpop.prefs

@{b}"Can't open ACTON prefs file"@{ub}

ASWPOP is trying to open the ACTON configuration file without success.. make
sure aswpop.acton is present in the directory set in ASWPOPPATH in the prefs
file.

@{b}"invalid path to INTERN script"@{ub}

The configured script for the matched INTERN does not exist where you have
told ASWPOP it does!! :-) Check aswpop.acton for the path you entered and
the path your script really exists..

@{b}"INTERN script is over 65k in size"@{ub}

INTERN scripts have a maximum size limit of 65k.. either your messing about
trying to get ASWPOP to read in and run a massive file, or you've programmed
an ASWPOP extension that is over 5 times to size of ASWPOP's source...
(WHY!?!!!)

@{b}"No settings file exists"@{ub}

s:aswpop.prefs cannot be found.. it is imperitive that this file exists..
copy it over from the ASWPOP archive

