@{b}Why write ASWPOP then?@{ub}
----------------------

Why? Because it was there to be done basically! I started off writing
ASWPOP as a simple way to separate mailing lists from my personal email...
bit by bit I built up the features list until it was turning into a full POP
client rather than a pissweed little script 'o shite!

Originally in version 0.1, the AREXX source was 3k in source.. now it stands
at over 10k.. And initially, the addition of the EXTERN and INTERN
capability was just some toy with which to impress the mates! haha..
little did I know it would open up lots of possibilities.

ASWPOP is only a baby, I started programming it only about 2 and a half
weeks ago!! Credit must go to Robin Evans for writing the excellent and
totally invaluable ArexxGuide... That guide made me the AREXX programmer I
am today. Without that guide, I'd still be tapping away writing pathetic DOS
scripts! :-)

I used Jonathan Gapen (jagapen@students.wisc.edu)'s useful (but sometimes
buggy!) POPd (comm/tcp/AmiTCP-popd.lha) for local testing, which saved me
armfuls of time and money by not having to log onto the net for lengthy
testing..

Basically, ASWPOP is a little sod about that's now turned into the biggest
program I've ever written!.. I am very pleased with the pace of development and
look forward to the future!

I hope it works for you as well as it's been working for me..

