@{b}What is 'IT' then?!@{ub}
-------------------

'It' or I is an 18 year old guy known to my friends as Andrew Walker (umm..
everyone else knows me as Andrew Walker too, strangely).. ASW is my IRC
nickname, built from my initials! (S being Stephen)

I live right on the South Coast of England, and am an absoulte Amiga fan!
I've taken my hardware all the way from a humble 1mb A500 with KS 1.3 up
to today's main machine which is a 50mhz 030 accellerated A1200 with 18mb's of
ram, a slightly smaller than I would like hard drive and a 14.4 modem which I use
to link up to the net much more than should be medically recommended! It's
actually quite a surprise I'm not 'multitasking' myself between writing this
guide and tapping away on the IRC! Perhaps I'm sick.. I do not know!

I'm currently floating in life after dropping out of my A-Level studies last
year (it was a strategic move: leave now, or be kicked out later!), but to
sort myself out, I've just applied for a two year course in programming..
I am very keen to learn C, as it would be a natural progression from AREXX..
I am programming in quite a modular fashion now, and am ready to make the jump!
I've actually bought a compiler and a "total dickheads guide to programming in
C" book, but haven't been motivated enough to get my head stuck into it! I
also plan to take a bit of a break in the US sometime this summer.. I have
quite a few netty friends over there and would like to get away from the
monotiny of this place! I'm a bit on the poor side though, what with looming
bills and debts! but never mind, I'll attempt to crowbar a few quid out of
my parents pockets for it! After all, it's all in a good cause, right kids?!

<ahem> anyway, ASWPOP is the latest in a line of ASW productions, and is sadly
one of the only ones near a stage of completeness! In the past, I've always
seemed to find a new project to concentrate on before finishing off the
previous project!! hey, ho.. they might get finished after I've tidied ASWPOP
up a little more..

