@{b}What other ASW projects are there!?@{ub}
-----------------------------------

I actually have quite a few ASW programs that are yet unfinished.. perhaps
after ASWPOP, I'll return my efforts to polishing them up.. amongst others,
the main projects are:

@{b}ASW-FTP@{ub}
-------

No, this isn't a standalone FTP client.. :-) That is one thing I think is
past the abilities of an AREXX program!! (who knows though, I'll have to
get hold of the FTP RFC and look into it!) No, ASWFTP is simply a script
that allows you to set up a queue of files to be FTP'd that will be pulled
with one command when online.. it requires ncftp, and is quite unfinished :)
It works though, and if ever I need a file from the Aminet daily, I use aswftp
to get it..

@{b}ASW-TAG@{ub}
-------

Now, this is an interesting one! You create a file containing names, a file
containing actions, perhaps another set of names, a funny remark or more, and
ASWTAG selects a line from each file at random, pastes them together, appends
the chunk to a file, and calls your editor to edit it.. Yes, ASWTAG is a random
tagline generator! It works, it's fast and it's a good example of AREXX
coding! :-) This one is quite near a release state, so you might see it on the
shelves, fans! :-)

@{b}Spit@{ub}
----

This one is insane! :) by far the most ambitious AREXX program I've ever
written before.. You know that Fidonet tosser called Spot?? Well, Spit is
what wakes Spot up in the night with a cold sweat.. :-) YES..call it mad, call
it insane, call it pointless, but I've actually got a working Fidonet
tosser/editor system written in AREXX on my machine.... it works, but it's
incredibly teadious to use! :)

@{b}Slammail@{ub}
--------

After getting pissed off to the extremes with Mailkick, I decided I might as
well go out and write my own SMTP client.. Slammail was the product of this
rage, and although it works (I use it for sending emails), I wouldn't wish it
upon anyone else in the world! I might give this one a bit of developing in the
future.. who knows! :-)

Ooh, we've come to the end!! :-))

